Package org.dellroad.jibxbindings.pidf.held Description

JiBX bindings for HTTP-Enabled Location Delivery (HELD).

This package includes JiBX bindings for the <locationRequest>, <locationResponse>, and and <error> XML tags used in the HELD protocol as described by RFC 5985. The binding name defined here is "held".

The concrete mappings defined are:

held:locationRequest
<locationRequest> element; represented by LocationRequest.
held:locationResponse
<locationResponse> element; represented by LocationResponse.
held:error
<error> element; represented by Error.

The type-names listed above use the following XML namespace prefixes:

held
urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:geopriv:held

See Also:
RFC 5985, JiBX Bindings
